FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS
A. END USER (Member)
FR-USER-001: Authentication & Identity

FR-USER-001.1: The system shall allow users to authenticate using OAuth2/OIDC providers.

FR-USER-001.2: The system shall allow users to log in and log out of active sessions.

FR-USER-001.3: The system shall allow users to terminate all active sessions.

FR-USER-001.4: The system shall allow users to view and update non-sensitive profile information.

FR-USER-002: Tenant Membership

FR-USER-002.1: The system shall allow a user to create a new tenant.

FR-USER-002.2: The system shall allow users to join a tenant via invitation.

FR-USER-002.3: The system shall allow users to belong to multiple tenants.

FR-USER-002.4: The system shall allow users to switch active tenant context.

FR-USER-002.5: The system shall prevent users from accessing tenants they do not belong to.

FR-USER-003: Project Management

FR-USER-003.1: The system shall allow users to create projects within an active tenant.

FR-USER-003.2: The system shall allow users to view projects they are authorized to access.

FR-USER-003.3: The system shall allow users to update projects based on assigned permissions.

FR-USER-003.4: The system shall allow users to delete projects based on assigned permissions.

FR-USER-003.5: The system shall prevent access to projects outside the active tenant.

FR-USER-004: File Management

FR-USER-004.1: The system shall allow users to upload files to authorized projects.

FR-USER-004.2: The system shall allow users to download files they are authorized to access.

FR-USER-004.3: The system shall allow users to view file metadata.

FR-USER-004.4: The system shall allow users to delete files based on permissions.

FR-USER-004.5: The system shall prevent access to files across tenants.

B. TENANT ADMIN
FR-ADMIN-001: User & Role Management

FR-ADMIN-001.1: The system shall allow tenant admins to invite users.

FR-ADMIN-001.2: The system shall allow tenant admins to remove users.

FR-ADMIN-001.3: The system shall allow tenant admins to assign and update roles.

FR-ADMIN-001.4: The system shall revoke access immediately when a user is removed.

FR-ADMIN-002: Tenant Configuration

FR-ADMIN-002.1: The system shall allow tenant admins to update tenant settings.

FR-ADMIN-002.2: The system shall allow tenant admins to create, rotate, and revoke API tokens.

FR-ADMIN-002.3: The system shall allow tenant admins to define default role permissions.

FR-ADMIN-002.4: The system shall allow tenant admins to suspend tenant activity.

FR-ADMIN-003: Monitoring & Audit

FR-ADMIN-003.1: The system shall allow tenant admins to view audit logs scoped to their tenant.

FR-ADMIN-003.2: The system shall allow filtering audit logs by user, action, and time.

FR-ADMIN-003.3: The system shall prevent admins from viewing logs outside their tenant.

C. DEVELOPER (API CONSUMER)
FR-DEV-001: API Credentials

FR-DEV-001.1: The system shall allow generation of tenant-scoped API tokens.

FR-DEV-001.2: The system shall allow revocation of API tokens.

FR-DEV-001.3: The system shall allow rotation of API tokens.

FR-DEV-001.4: The system shall log API token usage.

FR-DEV-002: API Operations

FR-DEV-002.1: The system shall allow CRUD operations on projects via API.

FR-DEV-002.2: The system shall allow file management via API.

FR-DEV-002.3: The system shall enforce the same authorization rules for API and UI access.

FR-DEV-002.4: The system shall allow querying tenant-scoped audit logs via API.

D. SYSTEM ADMIN (Platform)
FR-SYS-001: Platform Control

FR-SYS-001.1: The system shall allow system admins to view and manage all tenants.

FR-SYS-001.2: The system shall allow system admins to view platform health metrics.

FR-SYS-001.3: The system shall allow access to global audit logs.

FR-SYS-001.4: The system shall allow emergency user or tenant lockout.

FR-SYS-001.5: The system shall restrict system admin actions to a limited set of users.

E. LIFECYCLE & STATE REQUIREMENTS

Tenants shall have states: active, suspended, deleted.

Projects shall have states: active, archived, deleted.

API tokens shall have states: active, revoked, expired.

Invitations shall have states: pending, accepted, expired.
